{"title_page": "Nunor Bora", "text_new": "{{Infobox food\n| name             =  Nunor Bora\n| image            =  \n| caption          = \n| alternate_name   =  Nungora\n| region           = [[Sylhet region]]\n| country          = {{flag|Bangladesh}}\n| course           = Breakfast and light refreshment\n| type             = [[Savoury (dish)|savoury]]\n| served           =\n| main_ingredient  = onion, ginger, rice flour and turmeric\n| variations       = \n| other            =\n}}\n'''Nunor Bora''' ([[Sylheti Nagri]]: {{font|\ua818\ua825\ua818\ua827\ua81e \ua81b\ua81e\ua823|font=Surma|size=18px}}), also known as '''Nungora''' is a savoury [[rice flour]] [[snacks]] made of onion, ginger and turmeric that gives the snack its golden appearance.<ref name= dsi>{{citenews|url=https://www.desiblitz.com/content/sweet-and-savoury-snacks-enjoyed-in-a-bengali-household|title=Sweet and Savoury Snacks Enjoyed in a Bengali Household|date=November 28, 2018| access-date=25 April 2020| publisher=desiblitz.com}}</ref> It is also known as Nuniya Pitha in [[Bangladesh]]. It is a traditional and a popular Pitha in [[Sylhet region|Sylhet]].<ref name=\"bdp\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bd-pratidin.com/life/2016/08/18/164157|title=\u09b0\u09c7\u09b8\u09bf\u09aa\u09bf: \u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be|newspaper=[[Bangladesh Pratidin]]|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=18 Aug 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"jago\">{{cite news|url=https://www.jagonews24.com/lifestyle/article/543199|title=\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be \u09a4\u09c8\u09b0\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09ac\u09c7\u09a8 \u09af\u09c7\u09ad\u09be\u09ac\u09c7|newspaper=[[jagonews24.com]]|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=1 Dec 2019}}</ref><ref >{{cite news|url=http://www.independent24.com/details/61365|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7 \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be \u0989\u09ce\u09b8\u09ac|newspaper=Independent Television LTD|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=1 Dec 2019}}</ref> It is eaten with [[tea]] as a snacks and very popular on the [[Eid]] festival to the [[Sylhetis]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://samakal.com/bangladesh/article/140775604/\u09b9\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6-\u0993-\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u09b0-\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a6\u09c7-\u0988\u09a6-\u0986\u09a8\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6?|title='\u09b9\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6' \u0993 '\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be'\u09b0 \u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a6\u09c7 \u0988\u09a6 \u0986\u09a8\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\n|newspaper=[[Samakal]]|language= bn| access-date=27 July 2014|date= 16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Ingredients ==\n[[Onions]], [[ginger]], [[salt]], turmeric, [[panch puran]] (optional), rice flour, ground rice, chopped [[coriander]] (optional) and [[water]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.afeliaskitchen.com/nunor-bora/|title=Nunor Bora|website=Afelia's Kitchen|date=16 Aug 2016|access-date=25 April 2020}}</ref> \n== Method ==\nFirst, it is started by boiling water in a large [[saucepan]]. Then blended ingredients (onion, ginger, [[garlic]]) are added to the boiling water with some salt and turmeric powder.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.odhikar.news/life-style/food/108274|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u0990\u09a4\u09bf\u09b9\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09c0 \u2018\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be|newspaper=www.odhikar.news|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=2 Dec 2019}}</ref> Last ingredient is ground panch puran which adds a mouthwatering taste and aroma. But this ingredient is optional.\nA combination of plain flour, rice [[flour]] and/or ground rice is added to make a spongy soft paste by cooking. When the paste is fully cooked, they are taken out of the pan and allowed to cool.<ref name=\"syl1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/northamerica/article/1578099/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A0%E0%A6%BE|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be|newspaper=[[Prothom Alo]]|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=8 Feb 2019}}</ref> To form a ball of [[dough]] it is mixed. Then taking a ball of dough, it is rolled to make bread.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.findglocal.com/BD/Dhaka/498221866947173/Homemade-Recipe-Collection|title=Homemade Recipe Collection|newspaper=www.findglocal.com|date=| access-date=25 April 2020}}</ref> Cutting the bread into pieces, the Nunor Bora is shaped. Frying them in deep fried oil, this rice cake is made.<ref name= dsi/> Nunor Bora can be stored for a later usage without frying.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.daily-bangladesh.com/%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%9F%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A0%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BE/151879|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u099c\u09a8\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be \u2018\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u2019|newspaper=www.daily-bangladesh.com|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=22 Dec 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Pitha]]\n* [[Bangladeshi cuisine]]\n{{portal|Food}}\n{{Template:Bangladeshi dishes}}\n{{Sylhet topics}}\n[[Category:Sylheti cuisine]]\n[[Category:Courses (meal)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox food\n| name             =  Nunor Bora\n| image            =  \n| caption          = \n| alternate_name   =  Nungora\n| region           = [[Sylhet region]]\n| country          = {{flag|Bangladesh}}\n| course           = Breakfast and light refreshment\n| type             = [[Savoury (dish)|savoury]]\n| served           =\n| main_ingredient  = onion, ginger, rice flour and turmeric\n| variations       = \n| other            =\n}}\n'''Nunor Bora''' ([[Sylheti Nagri]]: {{font|\ua818\ua825\ua818\ua827\ua81e \ua81b\ua81e\ua823|font=Surma|size=18px}}), also known as '''Nungora''' is a savoury [[rice flour]] [[snacks]] made of onion, ginger and turmeric that gives the snack its golden appearance.<ref name= dsi>{{citenews|url=https://www.desiblitz.com/content/sweet-and-savoury-snacks-enjoyed-in-a-bengali-household|title=Sweet and Savoury Snacks Enjoyed in a Bengali Household|date=November 28, 2018| access-date=25 April 2020| publisher=desiblitz.com}}</ref> It is also known as Nuniya Pitha in [[Bangladesh]]. It is a traditional and a popular Pitha in [[Sylhet region|Sylhet]].<ref name=\"bdp\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bd-pratidin.com/life/2016/08/18/164157|title=\u09b0\u09c7\u09b8\u09bf\u09aa\u09bf: \u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be|newspaper=[[Bangladesh Pratidin]]|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=18 Aug 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"jago\">{{cite news|url=https://www.jagonews24.com/lifestyle/article/543199|title=\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be \u09a4\u09c8\u09b0\u09bf \u0995\u09b0\u09ac\u09c7\u09a8 \u09af\u09c7\u09ad\u09be\u09ac\u09c7|newspaper=[[jagonews24.com]]|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=1 Dec 2019}}</ref><ref >{{cite news|url=http://www.independent24.com/details/61365|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7 \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be \u0989\u09ce\u09b8\u09ac|newspaper=Independent Television LTD|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=1 Dec 2019}}</ref> It is eaten with [[tea]] as a snacks and very popular on the [[Eid]] festival to the [[Sylhetis]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://samakal.com/bangladesh/article/140775604/\u09b9\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6-\u0993-\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u09b0-\u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a6\u09c7-\u0988\u09a6-\u0986\u09a8\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6?|title='\u09b9\u09be\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\u09c7\u09b6' \u0993 '\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be'\u09b0 \u09b8\u09cd\u09ac\u09be\u09a6\u09c7 \u0988\u09a6 \u0986\u09a8\u09a8\u09cd\u09a6\n|newspaper=[[Samakal]]|language= bn| access-date=27 July 2014|date= 16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Ingredients ==\n[[Onions]], [[ginger]], [[salt]], turmeric, [[panch puran]] (optional), rice flour, ground rice, chopped [[coriander]] (optional) and [[water]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.afeliaskitchen.com/nunor-bora/|title=Nunor Bora|website=Afelia's Kitchen|date=16 Aug 2016|access-date=25 April 2020}}</ref> \n== Method ==\nFirst, it is started by boiling water in a large [[saucepan]]. Then blended ingredients (onion, ginger, [[garlic]]) are added to the boiling water with some salt and turmeric powder.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.odhikar.news/life-style/food/108274|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u0990\u09a4\u09bf\u09b9\u09cd\u09af\u09ac\u09be\u09b9\u09c0 \u2018\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be|newspaper=www.odhikar.news|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=2 Dec 2019}}</ref> Last ingredient is ground panch puran which adds a mouthwatering taste and aroma. But this ingredient is optional.\nA combination of plain flour, rice [[flour]] and/or ground rice is added to make a spongy soft paste by cooking. When the paste is fully cooked, they are taken out of the pan and allowed to cool.<ref name=\"syl1\">{{cite news|url=https://www.prothomalo.com/northamerica/article/1578099/%E0%A6%B6%E0%A7%80%E0%A6%A4%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A0%E0%A6%BE|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u09c7\u09b0 \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be|newspaper=[[Prothom Alo]]|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=8 Feb 2019}}</ref> To form a ball of [[dough]] it is mixed. Then taking a ball of dough, it is rolled to make bread.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.findglocal.com/BD/Dhaka/498221866947173/Homemade-Recipe-Collection|title=Homemade Recipe Collection|newspaper=www.findglocal.com|date=| access-date=25 April 2020}}</ref> Cutting the bread into pieces, the Nunor Bora is shaped. Frying them in deep fried oil, this rice cake is made.<ref name= dsi/> Nunor Bora can be stored for a later usage without frying.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.daily-bangladesh.com/%E0%A6%B8%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%B2%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%9F%E0%A7%87%E0%A6%B0-%E0%A6%9C%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%AA%E0%A7%8D%E0%A6%B0%E0%A6%BF%E0%A7%9F-%E0%A6%AA%E0%A6%BF%E0%A6%A0%E0%A6%BE-%E0%A6%A8%E0%A7%81%E0%A6%A8%E0%A6%97%E0%A7%9C%E0%A6%BE/151879|title=\u09b8\u09bf\u09b2\u09c7\u099f\u09c7\u09b0 \u099c\u09a8\u09aa\u09cd\u09b0\u09bf\u09af\u09bc \u09aa\u09bf\u09a0\u09be \u2018\u09a8\u09c1\u09a8\u0997\u09a1\u09bc\u09be\u2019|newspaper=www.daily-bangladesh.com|language= bn| access-date=25 April 2020|date=22 Dec 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Pitha]]\n* [[Bangladeshi cuisine]]\n{{portal|Food}}\n{{Sylhet topics}}\n[[Category:Sylheti cuisine]]\n[[Category:Courses (meal)]]\n", "name_user": "UserNumber", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nunor_Bora"}
